Que 5) What is the difference between HTML and XHTML?
-------------------------------------------------------
HTML
HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is used to create web pages.
It is flexible and less strict about rules.
Tags sometimes do not need to be closed.
Attribute values can be written without quotes.
Example:
<p>Hello World
<br>
XHTML
XHTML (Extensible HyperText Markup Language) is a stricter version of HTML.
It follows XML rules, so syntax must be very strict.
All tags must be closed.
Attribute values must be in quotes.
Tags must be properly nested and written in lowercase.
Example:
<p>Hello World</p>
<br />
Que 6) What is the role of DOCTYPE in HTML?
--------------------------------------------
Simple Explanation
DOCTYPE tells the web browser which version of HTML the page is using. 🌐
It helps the browser display the webpage correctly.
The DOCTYPE declaration is always written at the top of the HTML document before the <html> tag.
Example
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>My Page</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Hello</h1>
</body>
</html>
Here:
<!DOCTYPE html> → tells the browser the page is HTML5
It ensures the browser renders the page in standard mode
Why DOCTYPE is Important
1️⃣ Tells the browser the HTML version
2️⃣ Helps the browser render the page correctly
3️⃣ Prevents the browser from going into quirks mode (incorrect rendering)
✅ Simple Interview Answer
DOCTYPE is a declaration placed at the top of an HTML document that tells the browser which version of HTML is
being used so the page can be displayed correctly.
Que 7) What if you remove <!DOCTYPE html> from your HTML?
----------------------------------------------------------------
If you remove <!DOCTYPE html>, the webpage will still open in the browser, but it may not display correctly.
This happens because the browser does not know which HTML version is being used.
What Happens When DOCTYPE is Removed
1️⃣ Browser enters Quirks Mode
The browser uses old rules to display the page.
2️⃣ Layout problems may occur
CSS and design may look different or break.
3️⃣ Compatibility issues
Different browsers may show the page differently.
4️⃣ Harder debugging
Developers may face problems while fixing errors.
Example Without DOCTYPE
<html>
<head>
<title>Example</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Hello</h1>
</body>
</html>
The page may still load, but rendering may not follow modern HTML standards.
✅ Simple Interview Answer
If <!DOCTYPE html> is removed, the browser may switch to quirks mode, which can cause layout, compatibility, and rendering 
issues because the browser cannot identify the HTML version.
Que 8) Difference between Head & Body in HTML? Where to place JS link reference?
Difference between <head> and <body>
--------------------------------------------
<head> Tag
The <head> section contains information about the webpage.
This information is not directly visible on the webpage.
It is used for metadata and settings.
Common things inside <head>:
<title> – page title shown in browser tab
<meta> – page information
<link> – CSS files
<script> – JavaScript files
Example:
<head>
<title>My Website</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body> Tag
The <body> section contains the actual content of the webpage.
Everything inside it is visible to the user.
Examples of content:
Headings
Paragraphs
Images
Buttons
Links
Example:
<body>
<h1>Welcome</h1>
<p>This is my website</p>
</body>
Difference Table
Head	Body
Contains page information	Contains visible content
Not visible to users	Visible to users
Includes title, meta, CSS	Includes text, images, buttons
Where to Place JavaScript Link Reference?
JavaScript can be placed in two places:
1️⃣ Inside <head>
<head>
<script src="script.js"></script>
</head>
But this may slow page loading because the browser loads JS before the page content.
2️⃣ Best Practice – Before </body>
<body>
<h1>Hello</h1>
<script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
✔ This is recommended because the page loads first, then JavaScript runs.
✅ Simple Interview Answer
The <head> tag contains metadata and page information that is not visible to users, while the <body> tag contains the visible
content of the webpage. JavaScript files are usually placed before the closing </body> tag for better page loading performance. 🚀

Que 9) What is Title Tag in HTML? What are the 4 advantages of Title tag?
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Title Tag in HTML
The Title tag (<title>) is used to define the title of a web page.
It is written inside the <head> section of an HTML document.
The title appears in the browser tab when you open a webpage.
Example
<head>
<title>My First Website</title>
</head>
Here “My First Website” will appear in the browser tab.
4 Advantages of Title Tag
1️⃣ Shows Page Title in Browser
It displays the name of the webpage on the browser tab.
2️⃣ Helps in SEO (Search Engine Optimization)
Search engines like Google use the title to understand the webpage.
3️⃣ Helps Users Identify the Page
Users can easily know what the page is about.
4️⃣ Useful for Bookmarking
When users bookmark a page, the title becomes the bookmark name.
✅ Simple Interview Answer
The Title tag in HTML defines the title of a webpage and is placed inside the head section. It appears in the browser tab 
and helps with SEO, user understanding, and bookmarking of the webpage. 🚀
Que 10) What are Meta Tags? What are the 5 types of meta tags?
---------------------------------------------------------
Meta tags are HTML tags that provide information about a webpage to the browser and search engines.
They are written inside the <head> section of an HTML document and are not visible on the webpage.
Meta tags help with:
SEO
Page description
Character encoding
Mobile responsiveness
Example
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="description" content="HTML tutorial">
<meta name="keywords" content="HTML, CSS, JavaScript">
<meta name="author" content="Mahesh">
</head>
5 Types of Meta Tags
1️⃣ Charset Meta Tag
Defines the character encoding used in the webpage.
Example
<meta charset="UTF-8">
2️⃣ Description Meta Tag
Provides a short description of the webpage for search engines.
Example
<meta name="description" content="Learn HTML easily">
3️⃣ Keywords Meta Tag
Defines keywords related to the webpage.
Example
<meta name="keywords" content="HTML, CSS, Web Development">
4️⃣ Author Meta Tag
Specifies the author of the webpage.
Example
<meta name="author" content="Mahesh">
5️⃣ Viewport Meta Tag
Helps make the website mobile-friendly.
Example
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
✅ Simple Interview Answer
Meta tags are HTML tags placed inside the head section that provide information about a webpage to browsers and search engines. 
The five common types are charset, description, keywords, author, and viewport meta tags. 🚀

