Que 30) What is a Fragment Identifier in a URL?
-------------------------------------------------
A fragment identifier is used to jump to a specific section of a webpage.
It uses the # symbol.
Example:
<a href="#section1">Go to Section 1</a>
And the target element:
<h2 id="section1">Section 1</h2>
Q. What is the purpose of the <base> element in HTML?
The <base> tag defines the base URL for all relative links in a webpage.
It is written inside the <head> section.
Example:
<base href="https://example.com/">
After this, all relative links will use this base URL.
Que 31) How do you add an external stylesheet in your HTML?
------------------------------------------------------------
You add it using the <link> tag inside the <head> section.
Example:
<head>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
This connects the CSS file to the HTML page.
Que 32) How do you open a link in a new tab?
---------------------------------------------
Use the target="_blank" attribute.
Example:
<a href="https://google.com" target="_blank">Open Google</a>
This opens the link in a new browser tab.
Que 33) How do you create an Email Link?
----------------------------------------
Use the mailto: keyword inside the href attribute.
Example:
<a href="mailto:example@gmail.com">Send Email</a>
When clicked, it opens the user's email application to send an email.
